  "prompt": "What are some tips on making it through the job interview process at PTC Therapeutics?",
  "response": "Here are some tips for interviewing at PTC Therapeutics:\n\n1. Research the company thoroughly\n- Understand PTC's focus on rare disease therapies\n- Know their key products and pipeline\n- Learn about their mission and recent developments\n\n2. Prepare for technical/scientific interviews\n- Review your relevant scientific background\n- Be ready to discuss research experience\n- Demonstrate knowledge of genetic therapies and rare disease treatment approaches\n\n3. Highlight relevant skills\n- Emphasize experience in biotechnology, pharmaceuticals, or related fields\n- Showcase problem-solving and analytical skills\n- Demonstrate adaptability and team collaboration\n\n4. Practice common interview questions\n- Prepare answers about your background\n- Have specific examples ready to illustrate your experiences\n- Be ready to discuss your career goals\n\n5. Show enthusiasm for the company's mission\n- Demonstrate genuine interest in rare disease research\n- Understand the potential impact of their work\n- Show alignment with PTC's scientific goals\n\n6. Professional presentation\n- Dress appropriately\n- Be punctual\n- Bring extra copies of your resume\n- Maintain positive body language\n\n7. Ask thoughtful questions about the role and company\n- Show genuine interest in the position\n- Demonstrate you've done your research\n\nRemember, specific interview experiences can vary, so these are general recommendations.",
